# ANYTHING WITH A RECORDED DIGEST GOES HERE.
#
# Git's autocrlf rewrites line endings on checkout. A digest-pinned artifact then hashes
# differently for the reader than for the author, and the reader's honest conclusion is that
# the file was tampered with. A digest that fails on clone is worse than no digest at all.
#
# This has now bitten this project three times in one day: the WELLness surfaces were
# protected by `* text=auto eol=lf` and survived; the C-2 fixture was pinned without
# protection and did not; and the C-2 explainer was pinned an hour after that fix with a
# rule scoped to fixtures/ only. The narrow rule was the mistake — protection scoped to the
# directory that happened to hurt, rather than to the property that matters.
#
# So: the whole tree, matching what beehive-WELLness does.
* text=auto eol=lf
fixtures/** -text
*.woff2 binary
